summary_lines = []
summary_lines.append('CRISPR dependency analysis summary for ds001_depmap')
summary_lines.append('')
summary_lines.append('I analyzed 50,000 cell-line records using only the local task bundle. More negative dependency scores were interpreted as stronger knockout dependency. Unless stated otherwise, effect estimates are mean(subgroup) minus mean(comparison) on the dependency-score scale, so negative effects indicate stronger dependency. Interaction estimates are the product-term coefficient from OLS models of the form dependency ~ base + modifier + base:modifier.')
summary_lines.append('')
summary_lines.append('Iterations 1-2 tested binary driver-like hypotheses for the oncogene dependency outcomes. "'`feature_009=1` was strongly associated with `dependency_BRAF` (effect -0.5552, p<1e-300), `feature_022=1` with `dependency_EGFR` (effect -0.3486, p<1e-300), `feature_024=1` with `dependency_ERBB2` (effect -0.4321, p<1e-300), `feature_014=1` with `dependency_KRAS` (effect -0.3075, p<1e-300), and `feature_027=1` with `dependency_RIT1` (effect -0.0955, p=1.55e-68). These main-effect hypotheses were all supported. Subgroup refinements showed the BRAF signal was strong in `feature_009=1`/`feature_011="skin"` lines, ERBB2 was further enhanced by `feature_010="her2_enriched"`, KRAS remained strong within both pancreatic and colorectal lineages, and RIT1 was enhanced in `feature_011="brain"` lines.'"')
summary_lines.append('')
summary_lines.append('Iterations 3-4 focused on "'`dependency_KIF18A`. The initial colorectal hypothesis was supported: `feature_011="colorectal"` lines were much more negative than other lines (effect -0.4680, p<1e-300). Interaction tests then showed that this dependency was enabled by `feature_035=1` (interaction -0.6822, p<1e-300) and `feature_028 >= 0.819` (interaction -0.6691, p<1e-300), while `feature_020=1` suppressed the colorectal dependency (interaction +0.5714, p<1e-300). The complete refined subgroup `feature_011="colorectal"`, `feature_035=1`, `feature_028 >= 0.819`, and `feature_020=0` had mean `dependency_KIF18A` -1.2990 versus -0.2530 in all other lines (effect -1.0460, p<1e-300). This was the strongest and most specific dependency pattern found in the dataset.'"')
summary_lines.append('')
summary_lines.append('Iterations 5-6 examined broader essential-gene-like outcomes. High "'`feature_016` (`feature_016 >= 0.964`) was associated with stronger dependencies for `dependency_POLR2A` (effect -0.1043, p=1.01e-179), `dependency_DHX9` (effect -0.0371, p=1.71e-24), and `dependency_TMED10` (effect -0.0369, p=2.52e-24). Low `feature_016` had the opposite direction for POLR2A (effect +0.1005, p=1.20e-166). Outcome-specific refinements were supported for `dependency_DHX9` with high `feature_016` plus high `feature_023`, for `dependency_TMED10` with high `feature_016` plus high `feature_026`, and for `dependency_RPL11` with high `feature_003`. The `feature_003 >= 0.428` by `feature_030=1` interaction for RPL11 was significant but modest (interaction -0.0390, p=7.43e-03).'"')
summary_lines.append('')
